void x2ap_timers_init(x2ap_timers_t *t,
    int t_reloc_prep,
    int tx2_reloc_overall,
    int t_dc_prep,
    int t_dc_overall)
{
  t->tti               = 0;
  t->t_reloc_prep      = t_reloc_prep;
  t->tx2_reloc_overall = tx2_reloc_overall;
  t->t_dc_prep         = t_dc_prep;
  t->t_dc_overall      = t_dc_overall;
}
```

This function itself looks safe - it's just initializing fields in a struct. The issue mentioned is "stack buffer overflow from unbounded copy into fixed-size local array **downstream** of function x2ap_timers_init". This means the overflow happens after this function is called, not in the function itself.

