The issue is about a stack buffer overflow from unbounded copy into a fixed-size local array downstream of function x2ap_timers_init. Let me look at the code more carefully.

The function x2ap_timers_init at line 30 in /repo/openair2/X2AP/x2ap_timers.c is:

```c
void x2ap_timers_init(x2ap_timers_t *t,
    int t_reloc_prep,
    int tx2_reloc_overall,
    int t_dc_prep,
    int t_dc_overall)
{
  t->tti               = 0;
  t->t_reloc_prep      = t_reloc_prep;
  t->tx2_reloc_overall = tx2_reloc_overall;
  t->t_dc_prep         = t_dc_prep;
  t->t_dc_overall      = t_dc_overall;
}
```

This function itself looks safe - it's just initializing a struct with some integer values. The issue mentions "stack buffer overflow from unbounded copy into fixed-size local array downstream of function x2ap_timers_init", which means the overflow happens after this function is called, not necessarily in this function itself.

Let me look at the caller context in x2ap_eNB.c around line 317:

```c
    x2ap_timers_init(&new_instance->timers,
                     x2ap_register_eNB->t_reloc_prep,
